  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DRC - Support to ICRC&apos;s activities in South Sudan, 2014</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In South Sudan ICRC works to ensure that people affected by armed conflicts are protected in accordance with International Humanitarian Law, have access to medical/surgical care, physical rehabilitation and safe water, receive emergency relief and livelihood support, and can restore contact with relatives. Furthermore, it visits detainees and seeks to increase knowledge of IHL among the authorities, armed forces and other weapon bearers. In December 2013 clashes erupted in South Sudan&#xBF;s capital, Juba, and the fighting spread to Jonglei, Unity and upper Nile states, fuelling inter-ethnic violence. ICRC subsequently issued a Budget Extension Appeal, and has stepped up its operations, together with South Sudan Red Cross, addressing the increased emergency needs of the conflict-affected people, including in areas accessible to few/no other actors.</narrative>
  </description>
